<paragraph blockId="21.[192,1440,1480,1728]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,333,1480,1504]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Definition.</emphasis>
A sister genus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, [1870]" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1870" box="[533,835,1480,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[533,668,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia</emphasis>
Butler, [1870]
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[847,898,1481,1505]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1787" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1787" box="[992,1349,1480,1505]" class="Insecta" family="Papilionidae" genus="Papilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nothus">
<emphasis box="[992,1161,1480,1504]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Papilio nothus</emphasis>
Fabricius, 1787
</taxonomicName>
), where these species were formerly placed, but separated from it by a prominent genetic distance consistent with how other genera are defined (
<figureCitation box="[549,617,1544,1569]" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="22.[192,275,1419,1441]" captionTargetBox="[193,1440,215,1384]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[192,1440,213,1385]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Figure 9. Genomic trees of Astictopterini and relatives. See Fig. 2 legend for notations." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3677253" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3677253/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). Keys to VI.31.B in 
<bibRefCitation author="Evans" box="[855,1011,1545,1569]" firstAuthor="Evans" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" refId="ref27329" refString="Evans, W. H. 1937. A catalogue of the African Hesperiidae indicating the classification and nomenclature adopted in the British Museum. British Museum (Natural History); London. xii + 212 p., 30 pl." type="book" year="1937">Evans (1937)</bibRefCitation>
and differs from its relatives by pale apical spot on ventral hindwing in cell R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[672,680,1591,1605]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">5</subScript>
-M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[713,722,1592,1606]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">1</subScript>
is in line with the spots in cells next to it (not offset strongly basad); uncus bulbous in ventral view, which gives tegumen with uncus a bowling duckpin shape; harpe widening distad, separated from ampulla; ventral hindwing ochreous with many small silvery spots, dorsal forewing brown with large orange-yellow spots. In DNA, a combination of the following base pairs is diagnostic: aly669.9.1:A231G, aly214.13.5:A98G, aly4389.5.1:G869A, aly 
<date box="[1004,1123,1704,1728]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" value="1329-04-13">1329.4.13</date>
: 
<specimenCode box="[1127,1190,1704,1728]" collectionCode="T" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">T479</specimenCode>
C, aly214.13.5:A97C.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="20" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[192,1440,1750,1806]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,1750,1774]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name is a feminine noun in the nominative singular, a fusion of the Latin words 
<emphasis box="[192,237,1782,1805]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Arg</emphasis>
[entum] (silver) and [g] 
<emphasis box="[520,594,1782,1805]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">emma</emphasis>
(jewel), for the shiny, silvery gem-like spots on the hindwing below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[192,1440,1827,1883]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,430,1827,1851]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Species included.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[488,541,1828,1852]" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Druce, 1910" authorityName="Druce" authorityYear="1910" box="[645,1014,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aurea">
<emphasis box="[645,860,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia aurea</emphasis>
Druce, 1910
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Miller, 1971" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1971" box="[1024,1436,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maesseni">
<emphasis box="[1024,1280,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia maesseni</emphasis>
Miller, 1971
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Riley, 1925" authorityName="Riley" authorityYear="1925" box="[192,621,1859,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mabirensis">
<emphasis box="[192,473,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia mabirensis</emphasis>
Riley, 1925
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1946" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1946" box="[686,1068,1859,1883]" class="Insecta" family="Hesperiidae" genus="Ceratrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="20" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bonga">
<emphasis box="[686,907,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="20">Ceratrichia bonga</emphasis>
Evans, 1946
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
